content.description: Start low and right of the crescent moon sloper rail. Either mantle the sloper rock over or do a big span to a crimp out right to be able to compress the sloper feature. A sit start is possible and adds a grade to the problem at V8/9.
content.location: Brown-striped boulder 30 feet left of the main trail from the Jabberwocky and up hill.

content.description:
Starts on a low flat jug ledge, climbs out right through crimps and slopers and requiring a lot of tension before culminating in a hard last move crux.  Probably the hardest climb in Moe's, and well worth the effort!

A nice hang that is shady most of the day as well.
content.location: Starts on the big low slopey/jug rail in the middle of the roof and climbs out right.

content.description:
Starts on the same low jug ledge as force of nature but follows the jug ledge left to some nicely shaped edges and a big flat dish hold at the end of the roof.  Then quest up the tall face to top out.  Real nice rock quality on this one.

The book draws the line as if it starts on the face, which would be around V2 if you start here and skip the roof.
content.location: Starts on the same hold as force of nature, but climbs left.
